		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Christian terrorism</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Christian terrorism</b> is <a href="/wiki/Religious_terrorism" title="Religious terrorism">religious terrorism</a> by groups or individuals, the motivation of which is typically rooted in an idiosyncratic interpretation of the <a href="/wiki/Bible" title="Bible">Bible</a> and other <a href="/wiki/Christian" title="Christian">Christian</a> tenets of faith. From the viewpoint of the terrorist, Christian scripture and theology provide justification for violent political activities.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
